From: Irfan <irfan@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] MIPS: Add CONFIG_XIP_KERNEL and CONFIG_XIP_PHYS_ADDR Kconfig options

Add the Kconfig plumbing for Execute-In-Place kernels on MIPS,
modeled on the ARM and RISC-V options. XIP keeps .text/.rodata/
.init.text in the (KSEG0-addressable) flash window and copies only
writable data to RAM, freeing the RAM that kernel text would occupy.

Restricted to 32BIT && !RELOCATABLE && !MAPPED_KERNEL && !SMP:
KSEG0 is an unmapped segment, so flash below 512 MiB is directly
CPU-addressable and no page-table fixups are needed (cf. RISC-V
xip_fixup.h), but the kernel must be linked at a fixed address.
---
--- a/arch/mips/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/mips/Kconfig
@@ -2610,6 +2610,37 @@
 config SYS_SUPPORTS_NUMA
 	bool
 
+config XIP_KERNEL
+	bool "Kernel Execute-In-Place from ROM"
+	depends on 32BIT && !RELOCATABLE && !MAPPED_KERNEL && !SMP
+	help
+	  Execute-In-Place allows the kernel to run from non-volatile
+	  storage directly addressable by the CPU, such as NOR flash.
+	  The kernel text section is kept in ROM (linked at the KSEG0
+	  view of the flash window) and only the writable data sections
+	  are copied to RAM by head.S at boot.
+
+	  Unlike ARM/RISC-V, MIPS needs no page-table fixups for this:
+	  KSEG0/KSEG1 are unmapped segments, so flash below 512 MiB is
+	  directly CPU-addressable.
+
+	  The kernel image cannot be compressed and flash wear/latency
+	  make this slower than running from RAM, but it saves the RAM
+	  the text/rodata would occupy.
+
+	  If unsure, say N.
+
+config XIP_PHYS_ADDR
+	hex "XIP kernel physical location"
+	depends on XIP_KERNEL
+	default "0x1fc01000"
+	help
+	  Physical address of the flash region the XIP kernel is stored
+	  in. Must be below 512 MiB so it is visible through KSEG0, and
+	  must match where the image is actually programmed. The default
+	  leaves 4 KiB at the start of the QEMU Malta boot flash
+	  (0x1fc00000) for a small bootstrap shim.
+
 config RELOCATABLE
 	bool "Relocatable kernel"
 	depends on SYS_SUPPORTS_RELOCATABLE
